	<h2>Achieve the Straight Smile You've Always Wanted</h2>
	<p>
		A straight smile isn't just about aesthetics; correctly aligned teeth are easier to clean, reducing the risk of cavities and gum disease. At Canary Dental Clinic in Surrey, we offer comprehensive orthodontic solutions, including <strong>Invisalign Clear Aligners</strong> and <strong>Traditional Braces</strong>, tailored to fit your lifestyle and clinical needs.
	</p>

	<h3>Invisalign: The Clear Alternative to Braces</h3>
	<p>
		Invisalign uses a series of custom-made, virtually invisible plastic aligners to gently shift your teeth into place. It is the preferred choice for adults and teens who want a discreet treatment option.
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Invisible:</strong> Most people won't even notice you are wearing them.</li>
		<li><strong>Removable:</strong> Take them out to eat, drink, brush, and floss normally. No dietary restrictions!</li>
		<li><strong>Comfortable:</strong> No sharp metal brackets or poking wires.</li>
		<li><strong>Predictable:</strong> We use 3D digital scanning to show you your projected results before treatment even begins.</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Traditional Braces</h3>
	<p>
		While Invisalign is fantastic, traditional metal or ceramic braces remain the most effective solution for complex bite issues or severe crowding. They are highly predictable and do not rely on patient compliance (since they cannot be removed), making them an excellent choice for children and younger teens.
	</p>

	<h3>Who Is a Candidate?</h3>
	<p>
		Whether you are a teenager ready for your first set of braces, or an adult looking to subtly correct a shift in your teeth with Invisalign, our team can help. We provide personalized assessments to determine which orthodontic system will yield the best results for your unique smile.
	</p>

	<h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
	<details>
		<summary>How long does Invisalign take?</summary>
		<p>Treatment times vary depending on the complexity of your case. Mild spacing or crowding can be corrected in as little as 6 months, while comprehensive cases may take 12-18 months. You must wear your aligners for 20-22 hours a day for optimal results.</p>
	</details>
	<details>
		<summary>Are braces or Invisalign covered by CDCP?</summary>
		<p>Orthodontic treatments, including Invisalign and braces, are currently <strong>not covered</strong> by the <a href="/cdcp-dentist">Canadian Dental Care Plan (CDCP)</a>. However, many private employer insurance plans offer lifetime orthodontic maximums. We can help you check your coverage!</p>
	</details>

	<h3>Start Your Journey to a Straighter Smile</h3>
	<p>
		Ready to transform your smile? Schedule an orthodontic consultation with our <a href="/mandarin-speaking-dentist">bilingual team</a> to discuss your options.
	</p>
